## Reference
https://docs.python.org/2/library/string.html#formatspec
https://docs.python.org/2/library/stdtypes.html#str.format
https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#bin

1) Python's string format method can take a format spec: str.format()

>>> "{0:b}".format(2)
'10'
# 0 is the index of items in format; b is the type.

2) built-in lib: bin(x) - convert an integer number to a binary STRING. 
The result is a valid Python expression. 



